"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1167663","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-11-05","<p>The Ministry of Defence has no current plans to construct a dry-dock facility for the Queen Elizabeth Class aircraft carriers.</p><p>Plans for a long-term in-service support solution for the Queen Elizabeth Class aircraft carriers are under consideration as part of the Common Support Model for complex warships. However, on current plans, routine scheduled repair and refitting of the two Queen Elizabeth Class aircraft carriers, other than dry-docking, will be conducted at her Majesty's Naval Base Portsmouth and will sustain jobs at that site.</p>","Berwick-upon-Tweed","Anne-Marie Trevelyan","8279 ; 8280","2019-11-05T11:54:52.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1167663/answer","Biography information for Anne-Marie Trevelyan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1167663/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1167663/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-10-31","HMS Prince of Wales and HMS Queen Elizabeth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when he plans to announce the location for a new dry dock facility capable of housing HMS Prince of Wales and HMS Queen Elizabeth.","false","Biography information for Stephen Morgan","Portsmouth South","Stephen Morgan","8278"
